{"page_content": "![](https://saaq.gouv.qc.ca/_assets/3137b1a864c689786cac76b3def62dd1/Assets/img/default-banner.jpg)\n\n# Driver's Licence for Heavy Vehicles\n\nTo be authorized to drive a heavy vehicle, a driver must hold the appropriate class of licence and be in good health.\n\n## A heavy vehicle is...\n\n- A road vehicle with a gross vehicle weight rating (GVWR) of 4,500 kg or more\n- A combination of road vehicles with a gross combination weight rating of 4,500 kg or more\n- A tow truck\n- A road vehicle transporting dangerous substances requiring the display of safety marks\n- A bus\n- A minibus\n\n**Alcohol: 0.5 mg for drivers of heavy vehicles**\n\nIt is prohibited to drive or have the care or control of a heavy vehicle with a blood alcohol concentration equal to or higher than 50 mg of alcohol per 100 mg of blood (0.05).\n\nIf you drive a bus or a minibus, it's zero alcohol.\n\nTo find out more, go to the [Alcohol](https://saaq.gouv.qc.ca/en/road-safety/behaviours/drinking-driving) page.\n\nLast update: May 17, 2022\n\n## Safety first, on the road and online\n\nWe are committed to protecting your personal information and privacy. That's why, when we collect data, we follow a [Policy on Privacy](https://saaq.gouv.qc.ca/en/policies/privacy) that is responsible and transparent. By continuing to browse without modifying your preferences, you accept the use of cookies.\n\nEdit settingsAcceptReject\n\nDÃ©tection du zoom", "metadata": {"title": "Driver's Licence for Heavy Vehicles - SAAQ", "description": "To be authorized to drive a heavy vehicle, a driver must hold the appropriate class of licence and be in good health.", "url": "https://saaq.gouv.qc.ca/en/transportation-goods/drivers-licence", "language": "en", "keywords": "heavy vehicle, heavy truck, hvoo, licence, driver's licence, condition w, endorsement, competency, training, driver, truck, trucker, truck driver", "robots": null, "og_title": "Driver's Licence for Heavy Vehicles", "og_description": "To be a